					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's the point I disagree. Anyway, here my last $0.02:<br /><br />a) Is there a special reason for using the word &quot;dot&quot; instead of &quot;cycle&quot;?<br />b) The word &quot;pixel&quot; would count effective pixels from 1, and not from zero.<br /><br />I suggest to abandon the usage of &quot;dot&quot; as &quot;ppu cycles&quot;; just &quot;cycle&quot; is good enough, and it counts from zero. When saying &quot;pixel&quot;, it's always from 1.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I've used the terminology &quot;at x=256&quot;. Is that unambiguous?</div><br /><br />Since x can be zero, you mean the 257th rendered pixel.</div>

					
