				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To me dots are the timebase of the PPU, while pixels are the dots that actually paint something on screen, though I suppose that the video signal is always outputting <em>something</em> for every dot, like the background color, or the sync pulse. I think most people refer to only 256 of the 341 dots of a scanline as pixels.<br /><br />The benefit of &quot;dot&quot; over &quot;ppu cycle&quot; is that the latter is more verbose, not entirely clear, and will be shortened to &quot;cycle&quot; in discussion, which might then be confused with the CPU.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

